Patch Set 4:

That's a great catch i didn't see that.

In looking around I think that glance gets this wrong. glance is one of the few (only) projects that configures the admin project in oslo.config. When at least nova does this it does a policy check [1] and it does not lowercase it's roles first [2].

I can see similar behaviour in neutron (though it does something strange in context.elevated()), cinder and keystone (though this is not a good example as it has to work differently to other services).

I've put in a fix for the compatibility issue, but i think this is something that the glance team should probably address.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/8f5c2c0447886c6a2877ea9ca6484045d5597dd9/nova/context.py#L155
[2] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/8f5c2c0447886c6a2877ea9ca6484045d5597dd9/nova/api/auth.py#L138
